description:
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Patient Pathway Coordinator role is key to delivering an effective service to our patients. This role provides efficient and high quality administrative support to the Women’s and Children division, consultants and their teams, working in close co-operation with colleagues and other health professionals. Ensuring adequate support is provided to the Assistant Service Managers within the Women’s and Children division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to be organised and confident and be able to multi-task, prioritise work and lead with example. Previous experience as a patient pathway co-ordinator or medical secretary as well as One year’s experience in a supervisory position will be required. Working knowledge of NHS systems such as EMIS, RIO, PAS, CRS, EPR, DMS, G2 or any other digital dictation or patient information system will also be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a true team player with the necessary skills to provide a high standard of administration to this busy, high profile division. If you enjoy working as part of a team and have a flexible approach and professional attitude then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ayoku Balogun, Service Manager, Maternity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 0207 363 9084  EXT 3084 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: ayoku.balogun@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
